(234, 59, 'multiedit_ImageInfo', '<h4>COMPANY PROFILE</h4><p>Founded in 2004, CSP has been developing, implementing, and supporting custom technology solutions for corporate businesses that reside in our local community. Although our client''s corporate office may be local, many, have established satellite locations that are national, some even global. CSP has positioned itself to be able to support our client''s anywhere they need to establish a presense and with CSP''s ability to onboard quickly and streamline integration processes, our clients have been able to acheive their goals and see exponential growth. Our average client has a direct connection to many of the products and services most people use in the course of their day. If you buy products from Costco, get gasoline at Shell or BP, shop at Downtown Disney, or purchase movies from iTunes, then you''re seeing the results of work performed by CSP.&nbsp;</p>'),
(235, 59, 'multiedit_LeftRow1', '<h5>Michael Chen, Chief Executive Officer</h5><p><a href="http://www.csp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/michael.jpg" data-mce-href="http://www.csp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/michael.jpg"></a>Michael began his technology career in 1994 with Clayton, Williams and Sherwood, now CWS Capital Partners, a real estate investment management company managing and supporting their 50+ properties plus their nationwide network infrastructure. In 1998, Michael co-founded and was chief operating officer of ISPOT Interactive, a full-service web design and development firm for Fortune 500 companies. Michael worked with clients such as Business Objects (now SAP), Charles Schwab, and Agilent Technologies. In 2001, Michael decided to get back to his roots on technology infrastructure and networking. Michael worked at organizations such as the California State University and Ernst &amp; Young holding senior consulting positions. In 2004, Michael began his current venture and founded CSP, a technology solutions company that delivers end-to-end, comprehensive custom solutions for businesses through three focused avenues of technologies, Backup, Cloud and Networks.</p>'),
(236, 59, 'multiedit_LeftRow2', '<h5>Ryan Dillon, Chief Operating Officer</h5><p><a href="http://www.csp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/ryan.jpg" data-mce-href="http://www.csp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/ryan.jpg"></a>Ryan joined CSP in 2008. Ryan oversee''s the daily operations which includes corporate operations and client services. Prior to joining CSP, Ryan managed business units within organizations such as Beckman Coulter and Exemplis.</p>'),
